main event: Lt. Williams reported observing an unidentified object in the sky over Southern Wisconsin on the evening of 7 February 1953. The object appeared to be more than 50 feet in diameter, moved erratically, and exhibited an extra brilliant white light.
interesting points: The object was reported to be more than 50 feet in diameter, indicating a significant size.
It moved erratically, increasing and decreasing in speed, and exhibited an extra brilliant white light, indicating unusual behavior.
Weather at the time of observation was clear with visibility unlimited, which rules out natural atmospheric phenomena.
Observers were unable to estimate the size, altitude, or speed of the object, which adds to the mystery of the sighting.
The object did not register on radar screens at the station, suggesting that it had unusual properties.
sighted object: unidentified object in the sky over Southern Wisconsin
